WEBVTT

01:25.789 --> 01:35.020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.550 --> 01:37.940
[Episode 14]

01:40.460 --> 01:41.190
Over here.

01:41.590 --> 01:42.050
Come on.

01:46.950 --> 01:47.680
Boss!

01:48.560 --> 01:49.350
Boss!

01:52.070 --> 01:52.509
Give me a hand.

01:52.509 --> 01:53.640
What took you so long?

01:53.640 --> 01:55.229
I’ve been waiting so long
I’m about to get off work.

01:55.229 --> 01:56.780
Where is this?

01:57.200 --> 01:59.890
I want to go back to my dorm.

01:59.240 --> 02:01.360
[Registration Room]

02:00.060 --> 02:00.750
Baby,

02:01.000 --> 02:02.180
we are at the dorm.

02:02.290 --> 02:03.590
Let me tell your teacher,

02:03.590 --> 02:04.450
and we'll go in.

02:05.570 --> 02:06.350
Don't just stand there.

02:06.350 --> 02:07.750
Hurry up and get us a room.

02:08.300 --> 02:09.460
How much did she drink?

02:09.460 --> 02:10.590
Don’t stress, baby.

02:10.620 --> 02:11.420
Don’t stress.

02:11.460 --> 02:12.460
We'll go back now.

02:13.400 --> 02:14.820
Don't just stand there.

02:16.710 --> 02:17.329
Register.

02:17.620 --> 02:18.090
What?

02:18.190 --> 02:19.450
Why should I register?

02:19.870 --> 02:21.420
Don't you have to register
to stay in a hotel?

02:21.420 --> 02:22.720
Are you kidding me?

02:23.020 --> 02:23.840
Kidding you?

02:24.280 --> 02:26.210
You’ve gotta register to check in.

02:26.440 --> 02:31.500
[Registration Room]

02:27.060 --> 02:27.970
Okay.

02:27.970 --> 02:29.060
Hurry up.

02:31.840 --> 02:32.910
Don’t stress.

02:32.910 --> 02:33.840
What about hers?

02:35.960 --> 02:36.590
We’re together.

02:36.590 --> 02:38.250
Can’t we just register as one?

02:38.800 --> 02:40.579
You two are staying in the same room?

02:40.579 --> 02:41.410
Obviously.

02:42.470 --> 02:43.060
Marriage certificate.

02:43.060 --> 02:44.660
What marriage certificate?

02:44.930 --> 02:46.150
If you want to share a room,
you need a marriage certificate.

02:46.150 --> 02:47.810
No certificate, no same room.

02:48.280 --> 02:48.910
Bro,

02:49.560 --> 02:50.620
are you kidding me?

02:50.810 --> 02:51.590
Do I have nothing better to do?

02:51.590 --> 02:52.590
Those are the rules here.

02:52.190 --> 02:55.380
[Registration Room]

02:52.620 --> 02:53.750
Those are the rules.

02:54.470 --> 02:54.880
No.

02:55.090 --> 02:55.520
Don’t put on that big-shot act

02:55.520 --> 02:56.860
with me.

02:57.560 --> 02:59.120
Watch your mouth.

02:59.790 --> 03:01.560
I just won’t stay here, okay?

03:04.010 --> 03:04.800
Fine.

03:05.310 --> 03:06.710
You can go, but she can't.

03:06.740 --> 03:07.560
Why?

03:07.680 --> 03:08.620
Because she's drunk,

03:08.620 --> 03:10.020
and you're tricking her.

03:10.910 --> 03:11.810
I've seen robbers,

03:11.810 --> 03:13.060
but I've never seen kidnappers.

03:13.060 --> 03:14.680
Well today I am.

03:15.370 --> 03:16.800
The girl wanted to go back to her dorm,

03:16.800 --> 03:18.150
and you told her this is her dorm.

03:18.150 --> 03:18.860
Just because of this,

03:18.860 --> 03:20.750
I can't let you take her away.

03:21.250 --> 03:21.800
Kid,

03:22.470 --> 03:23.930
playing dumb with me, huh?

03:24.870 --> 03:26.130
Believe it or not, I'll kill you!

03:26.130 --> 03:27.650
Are you playing tough, huh?

03:27.650 --> 03:28.750
My guys are all here.

03:28.750 --> 03:29.810
What's wrong, Luo?

03:34.090 --> 03:35.750
Are you calling for backup, huh?

03:35.750 --> 03:37.430
I'm not bullying you today.

03:37.590 --> 03:38.579
We can settle this by the book—

03:38.579 --> 03:39.410
go to the station.

03:39.410 --> 03:40.400
Tang is there.

03:40.680 --> 03:42.010
Two options. Your call.

03:48.870 --> 03:50.600
Seasons Change Hostel, right?

03:51.120 --> 03:52.250
I'll remember this.

03:53.590 --> 03:54.690
You remember it!

03:56.460 --> 03:57.460
Are you okay, Luo?

03:59.620 --> 04:00.150
I'm fine.

04:00.910 --> 04:01.840
Go back, guys.

04:02.060 --> 04:02.660
All right.

04:18.430 --> 04:19.019
Miss,

04:19.190 --> 04:20.649
which school are you from?

04:20.980 --> 04:23.380
Do you remember the school's phone number?

04:29.120 --> 04:31.370
He just asked me to drink.

04:31.450 --> 04:33.330
He is not a good person.

04:33.680 --> 04:34.680
Yes, yes, he's not a good person.

04:34.680 --> 04:35.450
I can tell.

04:35.490 --> 04:36.270
I chased him away.

04:36.270 --> 04:37.000
Don't worry.

04:37.060 --> 04:38.060
I want to throw up.

04:38.870 --> 04:39.980
Don't throw up on the floor.

04:39.980 --> 04:40.500
Throw up here.

04:40.500 --> 04:41.100
Over here.

04:41.120 --> 04:41.920
Throw up here.

04:42.040 --> 04:42.700
Right here.

04:42.810 --> 04:43.740
Not on the floor.

04:48.480 --> 04:49.810
Are you feeling better?

04:58.450 --> 04:59.450
Sir.

05:01.060 --> 05:02.260
I'm not a teacher.

05:02.420 --> 05:03.150
I'm the boss.

05:04.010 --> 05:05.440
Are you okay now?

05:05.600 --> 05:08.200
-I want to sleep.
-Are you going back to school?

05:10.830 --> 05:12.480
I want to sleep.

05:13.070 --> 05:14.010
Wait, I...

05:18.180 --> 05:19.440
Come this way.

05:19.890 --> 05:21.120
Come on.

05:21.150 --> 05:21.830
Slow down.

05:22.720 --> 05:23.330
Easy. Come.

05:23.330 --> 05:23.980
Come on.

05:24.040 --> 05:24.540
Up the stairs.

05:24.540 --> 05:26.290
Stairs.

05:26.510 --> 05:27.410
Up the stairs.

05:27.660 --> 05:28.690
Go inside.

05:28.770 --> 05:29.510
Keep going.

05:31.720 --> 05:32.720
This way.

05:32.740 --> 05:33.180
Yes.

05:33.570 --> 05:34.570
Turn right.

06:24.540 --> 06:25.220
Get up!

06:25.500 --> 06:26.540
Stop sleeping.

06:28.100 --> 06:29.400
Who are you?

06:29.570 --> 06:31.030
Why did you bring me here?

06:32.470 --> 06:33.200
It wasn't me.

06:33.560 --> 06:34.540
I didn't bring you here.

06:34.540 --> 06:35.620
A guy named Zhao Gang

06:35.620 --> 06:36.830
brought you here.

06:37.010 --> 06:38.140
Do you remember now?

06:39.130 --> 06:40.810
He made you drink a lot yesterday,

06:40.810 --> 06:41.810
and got you drunk.

06:42.060 --> 06:42.930
He said my place

06:42.980 --> 06:44.080
was your dorm.

06:44.770 --> 06:45.480
He lied to you.

06:45.480 --> 06:46.159
I saw it wasn't right,

06:46.159 --> 06:47.330
so I kicked him out.

06:47.430 --> 06:49.159
And then you wanted to throw up.

06:49.450 --> 06:50.510
I said, "Go ahead,"

06:50.800 --> 06:51.740
and you did…
After that you sobered up a bit.

06:51.740 --> 06:53.220
You even called me "Sir,"

06:53.240 --> 06:53.920
remember?

06:55.080 --> 06:56.920
Then you said you wanted to sleep.

06:56.920 --> 06:58.000
I figured you couldn’t stay outside,

06:58.000 --> 06:59.430
so I let you sleep in the room.

06:59.430 --> 07:00.360
I stayed outside all night—

07:00.360 --> 07:01.220
got eaten alive by mosquitoes.

07:01.220 --> 07:02.260
I was outside.

07:02.390 --> 07:03.510
Many people can

07:03.540 --> 07:04.230
prove it.

07:04.870 --> 07:05.930
Then after I woke up,

07:05.930 --> 07:07.390
I thought you'd need to eat.

07:07.390 --> 07:08.770
So I went to buy breakfast for you.

07:08.770 --> 07:10.430
I didn't know what you wanted,

07:10.750 --> 07:11.870
so I bought a lot.

07:12.310 --> 07:13.540
You...

07:14.160 --> 07:14.680
Hurry up and eat up.

07:14.680 --> 07:15.620
Don't you have classes to attend

07:15.620 --> 07:17.150
or something after you eat?

07:17.160 --> 07:18.760
I'm going to sweep the floor.

07:31.060 --> 07:32.210
Eat up.

07:38.000 --> 07:38.800
Morning, Luo.

07:39.420 --> 07:40.320
Are you going out?

07:40.320 --> 07:40.940
Yes, Luo.

08:24.240 --> 08:25.370
You tried to be a hero

08:25.430 --> 08:26.860
and look at you now.

08:27.160 --> 08:28.570
I told you

08:28.620 --> 08:30.150
I wasn't trying to be a hero.

08:30.620 --> 08:31.820
He's taking revenge.

08:32.890 --> 08:33.690
Is she pretty?

08:36.840 --> 08:38.850
You really are getting old.

08:39.049 --> 08:40.289
I already told you.

08:41.080 --> 08:42.809
She's as beautiful as an angel.

08:44.510 --> 08:46.510
If you really have feelings for her,

08:46.600 --> 08:47.950
act like a man.

08:48.080 --> 08:49.550
Take action when you should

08:49.550 --> 08:50.810
and confess your love.

08:51.720 --> 08:52.580
You should know

08:52.870 --> 08:55.590
a girl with an oval face and phoenix eyes

08:55.870 --> 08:57.530
is liked by more than just you.

08:59.390 --> 09:00.940
It’s like

09:00.980 --> 09:03.180
Wu Xiaoshuai and Xia Tian in our script?

09:05.370 --> 09:07.180
The characters in the story

09:07.270 --> 09:08.840
have already done their best.

09:08.840 --> 09:10.100
But as screenwriters,

09:10.620 --> 09:11.800
we must be ruthless

09:11.890 --> 09:12.980
and twist the ending of the story

09:12.980 --> 09:14.180
into something else.

09:17.250 --> 09:17.960
Do you think

09:18.410 --> 09:19.820
wouldn't God dare to do

09:19.860 --> 09:21.590
what scriptwriters dare to do?

09:23.940 --> 09:24.840
God

09:25.440 --> 09:27.440
is the most ruthless scriptwriter.

09:33.370 --> 09:34.100
You know?

09:35.790 --> 09:36.250
Then...

09:36.480 --> 09:37.720
The conflict between you
and Director Weng,

09:37.720 --> 09:38.960
was it also a love rivalry?

09:38.960 --> 09:39.270
I...

09:40.910 --> 09:41.910
I and...

09:57.460 --> 09:58.130
Well...

10:02.630 --> 10:04.960
The girl with an oval face
and phoenix eyes

10:05.270 --> 10:06.670
was snatched away by him.

10:07.600 --> 10:09.790
Was she pretty?

10:11.850 --> 10:13.180
Very pretty.

10:14.390 --> 10:15.160
Tell me.

10:15.910 --> 10:17.130
Tell me, tell me.

10:18.940 --> 10:20.070
I'm not telling you.

10:26.390 --> 10:27.740
Your wiring’s all worn out.

10:27.740 --> 10:29.800
This won’t do; you need to replace it.

10:29.890 --> 10:30.700
Dongbei,

10:30.820 --> 10:32.110
you really should get your electricity

10:32.110 --> 10:33.120
fixed properly.

10:32.820 --> 10:42.060
[Guest Room]

10:33.120 --> 10:33.860
You go out first.

10:33.860 --> 10:36.100
The power’ll be back
once you come back in.

10:36.100 --> 10:38.010
Whether it gets replaced isn’t up to me.

10:38.010 --> 10:39.480
I've told the boss so many times,

10:39.480 --> 10:40.740
but he doesn't listen to me.

10:40.740 --> 10:42.270
Just make do with it for now.

10:43.720 --> 10:44.550
Ranran,

10:45.510 --> 10:46.130
in broad daylight,

10:46.130 --> 10:47.270
how much did you drink?

10:47.270 --> 10:48.130
Don't touch me.

10:49.040 --> 10:58.770
[Guest Room]

10:50.860 --> 10:52.660
Hurry back to your room and rest.

10:53.340 --> 10:54.340
Drink some water.

10:54.960 --> 10:55.690
Um, the tape.

10:56.440 --> 10:57.370
Give me the tape.

11:03.980 --> 11:04.910
What do you mean?

11:07.410 --> 11:08.630
Wait, are you going out again

11:08.630 --> 11:09.430
in this state?

11:09.960 --> 11:11.620
I’m just feeling frustrated.

11:13.200 --> 11:13.980
Ranran!

11:14.890 --> 11:15.360
Zhao.

11:15.360 --> 11:16.500
You shouldn't go out
when you're this drunk.

11:16.500 --> 11:17.480
Can you fix it or not?

11:17.480 --> 11:18.690
If not, let me fix it.

11:19.360 --> 11:20.690
I’m waiting to watch TV.

11:20.750 --> 11:21.270
Here.

11:21.370 --> 11:23.220
Little Northeasterner, here you go.

11:23.220 --> 11:23.670
Pliers.

11:23.670 --> 11:24.770
This month's rent.

11:25.240 --> 11:25.700
Take it.

11:27.670 --> 11:28.230
What are you doing?

11:28.230 --> 11:29.430
Stop messing around.

11:29.460 --> 11:29.910
My waist.

11:29.910 --> 11:31.170
Why didn't you go out for work today?

11:31.170 --> 11:33.070
My back is acting up again.

11:33.620 --> 11:34.240
Hey,

11:34.370 --> 11:35.300
go out for a walk.

11:35.960 --> 11:36.520
Why?

11:37.890 --> 11:38.580
Ranran

11:39.440 --> 11:40.270
drank too much.

11:40.270 --> 11:41.470
Something feels off.

11:41.750 --> 11:42.480
I hope nothing bad happens.

11:42.480 --> 11:43.130
Go check on her.

11:43.130 --> 11:45.260
What's wrong? Did she audition again?

11:46.120 --> 11:47.910
I don't understand things in your circle.

11:47.910 --> 11:48.500
Hurry up and check on her.

11:48.500 --> 11:49.840
She went towards the lake.

11:49.840 --> 11:50.500
Go quickly.

12:07.820 --> 12:08.550
Little girl,

12:09.460 --> 12:11.290
it’s so early—how’d you get this drunk?

12:11.290 --> 12:11.760
Come on,

12:11.790 --> 12:12.890
let me take you somewhere to rest.

12:12.890 --> 12:13.450
Let's go.

12:13.630 --> 12:14.690
What are you doing?

12:14.860 --> 12:16.000
Hey, who are you?

12:16.200 --> 12:17.260
I... I am her uncle.

12:18.440 --> 12:18.910
Her uncle?

12:18.910 --> 12:19.840
What do you want?

12:20.010 --> 12:21.340
Fine, you are her uncle.

12:21.860 --> 12:23.320
You are not behaving well.

12:23.670 --> 12:24.670
Go home right now!

12:25.240 --> 12:27.170
What are you wandering around for?

12:53.380 --> 12:54.770
You sit right here.

12:55.290 --> 12:56.050
Don't move.

13:06.740 --> 13:07.120
Here,

13:07.940 --> 13:08.870
have some water.

13:10.010 --> 13:11.100
It'll sober you up.

13:14.510 --> 13:15.460
My son

13:16.340 --> 13:17.940
really loves drinking this.

13:18.790 --> 13:22.290
No matter how sad he is,

13:23.080 --> 13:24.940
a soda will cheer him up.

13:25.890 --> 13:26.700
Try it.

13:53.080 --> 13:54.520
Tell me,

13:55.620 --> 13:56.150
can I

13:57.220 --> 13:59.240
help you?

14:04.250 --> 14:06.760
If you really can't hold on anymore,

14:06.870 --> 14:07.670
just go back to your hometown.

14:06.940 --> 14:09.820
[Ice cream]

14:07.890 --> 14:09.710
Go find your dad and mom.

14:09.740 --> 14:11.640
Why can't I hold on?

14:11.720 --> 14:13.290
Why should I go back to my hometown?

14:13.290 --> 14:15.350
Why don’t you go back to your parents?

14:20.410 --> 14:20.770
Well,

14:21.270 --> 14:24.940
I think Beijing is pretty good.

14:25.770 --> 14:27.220
There’s hope here.

14:27.340 --> 14:28.860
I'm motivated to do anything.

14:28.860 --> 14:29.980
I’ve got plenty

14:29.980 --> 14:30.860
that I can do too.

14:30.860 --> 14:32.240
I'm a good actress too.

14:33.170 --> 14:34.580
Why make me go home?

14:34.750 --> 14:35.410
Yes.

14:36.510 --> 14:38.270
We all think

14:38.270 --> 14:39.530
you are a good actress.

14:40.770 --> 14:41.220
You are

14:41.220 --> 14:42.940
a very, very good actress.

14:50.940 --> 14:52.070
Don't stand there.

14:52.100 --> 14:52.760
Have a seat.

14:57.320 --> 14:57.890
Drink.

14:58.580 --> 15:00.480
Here, there's another bottle.

15:01.200 --> 15:02.750
I'll put it here. Drink.

15:03.550 --> 15:04.190
Drink.

15:10.860 --> 15:12.130
You are an extra.

15:14.360 --> 15:16.090
I want to play the leading lady.

15:16.960 --> 15:18.890
It’s not the same; you don’t get it.

15:19.130 --> 15:20.610
It's a circle.

15:20.910 --> 15:22.070
At the very top

15:22.120 --> 15:23.650
of this pyramid

15:23.650 --> 15:24.790
are the investors

15:24.820 --> 15:25.890
and producers.

15:27.200 --> 15:28.460
Around a dinner table,

15:28.770 --> 15:29.860
there’s a whole circle

15:29.860 --> 15:31.390
of girls just like me.

15:32.340 --> 15:33.500
They all want to be actresses,

15:33.500 --> 15:34.760
all want roles.

15:36.010 --> 15:38.010
And they’re even prettier than I am—

15:39.030 --> 15:39.890
better at talking,

15:39.890 --> 15:41.220
and better at drinking.

15:42.550 --> 15:43.890
What can I do?

15:46.240 --> 15:47.410
If I don't go,

15:47.410 --> 15:49.740
I won’t even have this little chance left.

15:49.790 --> 15:50.840
Since I came to Beijing,

15:50.840 --> 15:52.270
I feel like I'm a failure.

15:52.270 --> 15:54.080
I haven't got a single role

15:55.510 --> 15:57.570
and am still living in this basement.

16:19.200 --> 16:20.480
I don't understand

16:21.150 --> 16:22.580
that circle

16:24.370 --> 16:25.260
you mentioned.

16:27.000 --> 16:30.460
But if you want to compete,
then compete properly—

16:30.910 --> 16:32.230
be a good actress.

16:32.840 --> 16:34.440
Don't compete with them over

16:34.550 --> 16:35.870
who is more articulate

16:36.080 --> 16:37.360
or can drink more.

16:37.670 --> 16:40.100
Just strive to be a good actress, right?

16:41.000 --> 16:43.500
Anyway, all of us

16:44.050 --> 16:46.100
think you are a good actress.

16:47.790 --> 16:48.460
Besides,

16:48.820 --> 16:50.670
if hanging out with them

16:50.670 --> 16:51.730
makes you unhappy,

16:52.250 --> 16:54.300
then don't hang out with them.

16:54.500 --> 16:56.440
You can stay with us.

16:56.650 --> 16:57.140
Right?

16:57.630 --> 16:59.830
You come back to Seasons Change Hostel.

16:59.960 --> 17:01.720
It's so nice here.

17:01.740 --> 17:04.560
You have Zhuang Zhuang

17:05.000 --> 17:05.730
here, right?

17:05.770 --> 17:06.550
There's Xu,

17:07.200 --> 17:08.220
Cao,

17:08.690 --> 17:10.160
and Liangliang.

17:13.980 --> 17:15.240
With all these people,

17:15.660 --> 17:16.920
wouldn't you be happy?

17:21.829 --> 17:24.569
You say I'm an extra.

17:25.980 --> 17:27.109
But I have lines.

17:28.400 --> 17:30.080
I'm a guest actor.

17:30.380 --> 17:31.900
My line goes like this,

17:36.350 --> 17:37.780
"Charge!"

17:41.500 --> 17:42.690
This "Charge!"

17:43.160 --> 17:44.790
has helped me a lot.

17:45.660 --> 17:46.680
Every time

17:46.700 --> 17:48.180
I encounter difficulties,

17:48.180 --> 17:48.920
I just think,

17:50.750 --> 17:52.160
"Charge!"

17:56.640 --> 17:57.680
But kid,

17:58.700 --> 17:59.740
everything

17:59.960 --> 18:02.110
has a limit.

18:03.010 --> 18:05.010
When I first came to Beijing,

18:05.220 --> 18:06.020
I thought that

18:06.110 --> 18:08.390
as an extra

18:08.880 --> 18:10.820
I could make a few dozen yuan a day,

18:11.110 --> 18:12.420
and after a month

18:13.680 --> 18:15.080
I’d have over a thousand.

18:15.220 --> 18:17.510
If I just stuck with it for a few years,

18:18.440 --> 18:20.590
wouldn’t I reach my goal?

18:23.500 --> 18:25.030
I was being too optimistic.

18:26.160 --> 18:28.110
After a month,

18:28.200 --> 18:29.930
there’s barely any work at all.

18:30.500 --> 18:32.760
But I couldn’t just sit around like that,

18:32.920 --> 18:34.770
so I started wandering everywhere
looking for work.

18:34.770 --> 18:37.240
One day I passed by a construction site.

18:37.750 --> 18:41.090
They were carrying cement bags,

18:41.510 --> 18:42.310
so I asked

18:42.310 --> 18:43.610
how much it paid.

18:44.660 --> 18:45.770
They said,

18:46.090 --> 18:47.210
"Thirty yuan

18:47.460 --> 18:48.630
a day.

18:48.850 --> 18:50.290
Are you in or not?"

18:50.420 --> 18:53.250
I thought it over and over

18:55.480 --> 18:56.480
and still said no.

18:57.830 --> 19:00.000
I still have two mouths to feed.

19:00.640 --> 19:02.900
So I can't risk my life
just to make money.

19:03.530 --> 19:04.280
Beijing has

19:05.030 --> 19:06.480
so many opportunities.

19:07.570 --> 19:08.890
There's a lot of work,

19:09.110 --> 19:10.420
so there's hope.

19:12.220 --> 19:13.860
In a person's heart,

19:15.290 --> 19:17.540
there must be a line.

19:19.250 --> 19:19.790
Right?

19:21.290 --> 19:22.550
There must be a line.

19:32.310 --> 19:33.640
Are you falling asleep?

20:08.180 --> 20:09.840
Master, please wait a moment.

20:10.200 --> 20:12.180
The water is coming right up.

20:14.640 --> 20:14.970
Here.

20:21.160 --> 20:21.720
Sheng...

20:22.610 --> 20:23.330
Shengli.

20:28.930 --> 20:35.740
Shengli, this time
I really can't see anything.

20:41.830 --> 20:43.010
Master,

20:44.680 --> 20:45.670
are you hungry?

20:46.220 --> 20:47.660
I'll go cook for you.

20:47.720 --> 20:48.240
Okay.

20:57.850 --> 20:59.480
Master, dinner is ready.

20:59.590 --> 20:59.940
Okay.

21:01.480 --> 21:02.040
Okay.

21:03.140 --> 21:04.730
Today's dishes include

21:05.380 --> 21:06.380
braised chicken,

21:07.290 --> 21:09.070
and pork stewed with potatoes.

21:09.070 --> 21:09.570
Okay.

21:10.220 --> 21:12.080
Stir-fried sweet potato leaves.

21:12.350 --> 21:13.660
And twice-cooked pork.

21:13.660 --> 21:14.880
Okay.

21:16.680 --> 21:18.000
Here are your chopsticks.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.350
Okay.

21:28.090 --> 21:28.440
Here.

21:29.750 --> 21:30.090
Okay.

21:31.250 --> 21:32.550
Okay.

21:33.110 --> 21:33.590
Okay.

21:34.110 --> 21:35.290
Okay.

21:38.920 --> 21:39.350
Okay.

21:42.550 --> 21:44.420
I’ll get you some more
sweet potato leaves.

21:44.420 --> 21:44.750
Here.

21:44.980 --> 21:46.330
Okay.

21:49.050 --> 21:50.180
Twice-cooked pork.

21:52.530 --> 21:53.990
The boss at the market said

21:54.500 --> 21:56.430
your favorite sweet potato leaves

21:56.550 --> 21:57.880
are going out of season.

21:58.610 --> 21:59.660
But it's fine.

22:00.290 --> 22:02.000
It doesn't matter
if the sweet potato leaves are gone.

22:02.000 --> 22:02.680
There will be

22:02.680 --> 22:04.510
better vegetables on the market later.

22:04.510 --> 22:05.240
Is that so?

22:07.590 --> 22:11.140
It's so hard just to

22:11.610 --> 22:12.940
have a meal in this life.

22:19.460 --> 22:21.830
I'll cook for you anytime you want.

22:22.050 --> 22:23.380
Okay.

22:30.090 --> 22:31.260
Today I added

22:32.600 --> 22:34.800
the stories about you and Director Weng

22:35.010 --> 22:36.160
to our script.

22:36.880 --> 22:38.140
Do you think Director Weng

22:38.140 --> 22:39.530
will be mad at me?

22:39.680 --> 22:40.410
Go ahead,

22:41.220 --> 22:41.620
add it.

22:43.220 --> 22:44.450
Do you really think

22:44.830 --> 22:46.360
we’ve been holding a grudge

22:46.680 --> 22:48.140
over something that small

22:48.980 --> 22:50.290
for 20 years?

22:53.140 --> 22:54.420
Then why is it?

23:00.240 --> 23:01.550
Because that brat

23:02.740 --> 23:04.400
messed around with my script!

23:10.330 --> 23:10.980
Eat.

23:11.680 --> 23:12.110
Eat.

23:18.700 --> 23:19.090
Okay.

23:21.420 --> 23:22.080
Delicious.

23:27.460 --> 23:29.400
Didn't I alter your script too?

23:30.660 --> 23:32.180
Yes, you altered it well.

23:43.550 --> 23:44.130
Shengli,

23:48.980 --> 23:50.830
pick up a piece of potato for me

23:55.530 --> 23:57.180
and put it in my mouth.

24:06.350 --> 24:07.510
This is authentic.

24:12.830 --> 24:15.180
Is it easy to get a full meal?

24:34.940 --> 24:35.730
My mom said

24:35.810 --> 24:36.940
to wash this one too.

24:37.500 --> 24:37.880
Okay.

24:38.710 --> 24:45.870
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

24:39.010 --> 24:39.670
Put it here.

24:45.310 --> 24:46.480
What grade are you in?

24:46.480 --> 24:47.340
Seventh grade.

24:47.720 --> 24:49.650
You're about the same age as my son.

24:49.980 --> 24:51.030
You just finished your exams, right?

24:51.030 --> 24:51.940
How did you do?

24:55.140 --> 24:56.660
My son's grades

24:56.810 --> 24:57.860
are really good.

24:59.030 --> 25:00.290
Why do you talk so much?

25:00.690 --> 25:02.970
[Professional Repair
of All Home Appliances]

25:05.200 --> 25:07.070
You're not good at studying, huh?

25:11.090 --> 25:12.230
I haven't seen them

25:12.500 --> 25:13.830
for half a year.

25:23.270 --> 25:23.790
Master,

25:24.440 --> 25:25.330
if you go back to recover

25:25.330 --> 25:26.140
and need an extra hand,

25:26.140 --> 25:27.340
I'll go back with you.

25:27.640 --> 25:30.040
The factory will send someone
to escort me.

25:30.880 --> 25:31.790
If you go,

25:32.720 --> 25:34.720
who’s going to take care of
your food and lodging? It’ll cost money.

25:34.720 --> 25:36.330
I can take care of myself.

25:37.500 --> 25:38.570
I knew even if I told you,

25:38.570 --> 25:39.700
you wouldn’t agree.

25:41.380 --> 25:42.770
Good delivery.

25:42.980 --> 25:44.480
One line, two meanings—

25:44.700 --> 25:45.160
clever.

25:45.380 --> 25:46.780
I'm not lying.

25:47.010 --> 25:47.770
Just say the word,

25:47.770 --> 25:49.030
and I'll be right over.

25:50.660 --> 25:52.940
You... You have a lame leg,

25:53.090 --> 25:54.440
and I'm blind.

25:54.740 --> 25:56.560
If we stand on the street,

25:56.640 --> 25:58.530
people will think we're beggars.

25:58.590 --> 25:59.720
Isn't that perfect?

26:00.010 --> 26:01.160
I'll get you an erhu.

26:01.160 --> 26:02.220
We can earn our travel expenses

26:02.220 --> 26:03.020
along the way.

26:05.610 --> 26:08.140
I really don't need more hands right now.

26:09.350 --> 26:11.810
What I'm most worried about

26:12.090 --> 26:13.120
is just one thing.

26:13.200 --> 26:13.930
Don't worry.

26:14.810 --> 26:16.440
I’ll get it done—
on time and up to standard.

26:16.440 --> 26:18.330
You’re still missing a word… "well."

26:18.330 --> 26:19.550
I’ll get it done well—

26:19.550 --> 26:21.140
on time and up to standard.

26:22.330 --> 26:24.390
What I’m really worried about is you.

26:25.380 --> 26:26.440
Once you get there,

26:26.500 --> 26:27.510
let me know you're safe.

26:27.510 --> 26:28.310
Stop nagging.

26:29.740 --> 26:31.000
After I left,

26:31.590 --> 26:33.230
since your leg is bad,

26:33.500 --> 26:34.500
you can stay here.

26:34.920 --> 26:36.450
After you finish the draft,

26:36.660 --> 26:38.600
copy it out

26:38.700 --> 26:39.830
neatly and properly

26:40.330 --> 26:41.790
and give me your feedback.

26:41.920 --> 26:43.920
Who’d dare give you feedback?

26:44.830 --> 26:46.490
But I don't mind staying here.

26:48.700 --> 26:51.500
A young upstart can always
surprise an old master.

26:51.940 --> 26:53.200
You need to toughen up.

26:53.570 --> 26:54.100
Alright.

26:54.500 --> 26:55.630
Walk me downstairs.

26:57.850 --> 26:58.700
Toughen up.

27:01.310 --> 27:03.670
You must take good care of my books.

27:05.200 --> 27:06.310
Read more.

27:06.570 --> 27:08.560
You can only improve by reading.

27:09.180 --> 27:09.660
Got it.

27:10.940 --> 27:11.660
Shengli.

27:12.240 --> 27:14.820
It's not like you're not coming back.

27:15.010 --> 27:17.010
Why are you bringing so many things?

27:17.070 --> 27:18.200
I'll keep your books

27:18.310 --> 27:19.330
and read them.

27:20.440 --> 27:22.590
Who said I would definitely come back?

27:23.530 --> 27:25.060
What are you talking about?

27:25.070 --> 27:26.220
Once you’ve gotten used to
stuffed beef pancakes,

27:26.220 --> 27:27.700
plain steamed buns just
don’t go down anymore, right?

27:27.700 --> 27:28.410
Exactly.

27:28.570 --> 27:29.660
A nobody suddenly acting like a big shot

27:29.660 --> 27:30.610
after getting a bit of luck.

27:30.610 --> 27:31.870
Who can we complain to?

27:32.400 --> 27:34.060
There's nothing we can do.

27:34.160 --> 27:34.970
This

27:35.680 --> 27:36.270
is fate.

27:37.070 --> 27:37.500
Look,

27:37.960 --> 27:38.690
people say

27:38.960 --> 27:40.590
when one person reaches enlightenment,

27:40.590 --> 27:41.680
even their whole household benefits.

27:41.680 --> 27:42.070
No...

27:42.070 --> 27:44.470
-You’re bringing us along too?
-No, no, no.

27:45.200 --> 27:46.600
You want to get benefits?

27:46.920 --> 27:48.160
Be glad I didn’t drag you

27:48.160 --> 27:49.050
straight down instead.

27:49.050 --> 27:50.980
What? The eighteen levels of hell?

27:51.270 --> 27:52.400
Are you done?

27:52.400 --> 27:52.790
We're already

27:52.790 --> 27:54.510
on the first level underground.

27:54.510 --> 27:56.110
Seventeen more levels to go?

27:56.160 --> 27:57.980
Look at you all,

27:58.070 --> 27:59.220
all talk.

27:59.610 --> 28:01.260
Can you take some real action

28:01.290 --> 28:02.250
to show it?

28:02.400 --> 28:03.140
Show what?

28:05.090 --> 28:06.640
Let's give him a hug.

28:07.240 --> 28:08.270
Come, hug.

28:08.270 --> 28:08.940
Sure.

28:08.940 --> 28:09.610
Just say it,

28:09.610 --> 28:10.310
I'll give you a hug.

28:10.310 --> 28:11.700
No.

28:11.940 --> 28:12.750
You want a hug?

28:14.280 --> 28:15.850
I'll hug you first.

28:15.940 --> 28:17.340
Who’s going to hug first?

28:17.640 --> 28:18.240
Hug him right here.

28:18.240 --> 28:19.100
Give him a kiss.

28:19.590 --> 28:20.830
Come, give him a kiss.

28:20.830 --> 28:22.430
-I mean parting wine
-Get up.

28:22.460 --> 28:24.180
-and farewell dishes.
-Give you a hug.

28:24.180 --> 28:24.830
What?

28:24.940 --> 28:25.610
No,

28:26.310 --> 28:27.250
you're overthinking.

28:27.250 --> 28:29.090
I’m broke. My pockets are empty.

28:29.110 --> 28:30.570
I really don't have money.

28:30.590 --> 28:31.670
No.

28:31.810 --> 28:32.960
Look at you all,

28:33.050 --> 28:35.140
-Open the door!
-You ungrateful jerk.

28:35.140 --> 28:36.680
-Coming.
-Come on. Give me a hand.

28:36.680 --> 28:37.270
Coming.

28:39.530 --> 28:40.660
The dishes are here.

28:41.250 --> 28:43.070
I had Little Northeasterner prepare it.

28:43.070 --> 28:43.640
How is it?

28:44.830 --> 28:46.770
So we all benefit, right?

28:48.750 --> 28:51.970
Alright then, we’ll benefit together!

28:52.090 --> 28:52.960
Come.

28:53.000 --> 28:54.860
Hold on, let me check first

28:55.030 --> 28:56.350
whether this wine is any good

28:56.350 --> 28:57.240
and whether the food’s decent.

28:57.240 --> 28:58.440
Look, is this wine...

28:58.440 --> 28:59.420
Take a look.

28:59.510 --> 29:02.440
It's good wine.

29:02.920 --> 29:03.350
Okay.

29:03.610 --> 29:04.740
Okay, okay, come on.

29:05.570 --> 29:07.510
Let's drink until he can't leave today.

29:07.510 --> 29:08.310
Get him drunk.

29:08.610 --> 29:09.700
Yeah, get him drunk.

29:09.700 --> 29:10.590
Just get him drunk.

29:10.590 --> 29:11.750
We have to get him drunk today.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.680
It's hard to say who's getting who drunk.

29:13.680 --> 29:15.080
Who's getting who drunk?

29:15.240 --> 29:16.680
Are they getting you drunk?

29:16.680 --> 29:17.960
Th-they want to get me drunk.

29:17.960 --> 29:19.570
No, we wouldn't dare.

29:19.590 --> 29:21.110
Someone is protecting him now,

29:21.110 --> 29:21.570
right?

29:21.740 --> 29:23.550
If things go wrong,
she’ll flip the table on us.

29:23.550 --> 29:24.050
Right?

29:24.050 --> 29:24.910
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

29:24.910 --> 29:25.850
I'm not eating.

29:26.200 --> 29:27.510
I'll wait to eat with Ranran.

29:27.510 --> 29:28.880
Her stomach
hasn't been feeling well lately.

29:28.880 --> 29:30.610
What's wrong with Ranran? What happened?

29:30.610 --> 29:32.700
It's nothing serious. Don't worry.

29:32.750 --> 29:34.220
Does it have anything to do with you?

29:34.220 --> 29:36.110
Does it have anything to do with you?

29:36.110 --> 29:36.900
I don't want

29:36.900 --> 29:37.720
to eat with them anyway.

29:37.720 --> 29:38.790
-Let’s eat out.
-You…

29:38.790 --> 29:39.270
Okay.

29:39.790 --> 29:40.390
All right.

29:41.250 --> 29:42.200
Do you guys want anything to eat?

29:42.200 --> 29:42.700
No, thanks.

29:42.700 --> 29:44.750
Xu Shengli puts girls before his friends.

29:44.750 --> 29:46.270
You guys can go.

29:46.270 --> 29:46.550
Let's go.

29:46.550 --> 29:46.900
Go.

29:47.440 --> 29:49.640
Bring some millet porridge for Ranran.

29:50.110 --> 29:51.250
You're not being polite at all.

29:51.250 --> 29:52.090
I'll go make it for you?

29:52.090 --> 29:53.900
If we don't make him drunk now,
then who will?

29:53.900 --> 29:55.110
-You.
-Make you drunk.

29:55.110 --> 29:56.480
Don't make me drunk.

29:59.530 --> 30:00.190
Are you sad?

30:01.070 --> 30:01.930
Sad about what?

30:03.460 --> 30:05.520
Aren't you sad that I'm leaving here?

30:08.720 --> 30:10.670
What if I never come back?

30:11.050 --> 30:13.330
Life goes on with or without anyone.

30:14.960 --> 30:15.750
Be careful.

30:17.460 --> 30:18.320
Sit for a while.

30:18.640 --> 30:19.470
Don't worry.

30:19.660 --> 30:21.260
I will definitely come back.

30:27.310 --> 30:28.770
People always aim higher.

30:28.960 --> 30:30.690
I just hope you don’t come back.

30:31.510 --> 30:33.000
There you go again.

30:33.950 --> 30:35.680
But what will you do without me?

30:35.740 --> 30:37.000
I won't let myself starve.

30:37.000 --> 30:37.460
Then...

30:38.570 --> 30:40.220
What if others bully you?

30:43.590 --> 30:44.390
Don't worry.

30:44.940 --> 30:46.140
I can go to the police.

30:50.290 --> 30:52.520
I just want you to focus

30:52.660 --> 30:54.390
and write your script in peace.

30:54.770 --> 30:55.420
Everyone is waiting

30:55.420 --> 30:56.480
to watch your movie.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.080
It wouldn't delay anything.

30:58.220 --> 30:59.550
I didn't say it would.

31:00.420 --> 31:03.880
It's not like we'll never see each other
again after you leave.

31:08.660 --> 31:09.790
Will you come see me?

31:18.380 --> 31:20.480
I'll have to see how your recovery goes.

31:20.480 --> 31:22.140
Don't try to pin it on me later.

31:28.720 --> 31:29.850
Well, my leg

31:29.920 --> 31:31.010
isn't healed yet.

31:31.070 --> 31:32.790
Doesn't that mean you have to

31:32.790 --> 31:33.850
take care of me now?

31:35.220 --> 31:35.640
You...

32:04.180 --> 32:04.620
I...

32:05.740 --> 32:06.480
I sincerely hope

32:06.480 --> 32:07.950
you can use this good luck

32:08.030 --> 32:09.360
to keep getting better.

32:14.920 --> 32:15.670
We will both

32:15.960 --> 32:17.760
get better and better together.

32:25.700 --> 32:26.110
Okay.

32:36.550 --> 32:40.900
I've searched for you
over thousands of miles.

32:43.180 --> 32:45.310
Without a care.

32:45.400 --> 32:46.090
Hello, sir.

32:46.140 --> 32:46.680
I'm not...

32:46.680 --> 32:50.570
You don't seem to be in my dreams.

32:51.000 --> 32:55.920
But in my dreams you are my only one.

32:56.660 --> 32:57.610
Hello, sir.

32:58.310 --> 32:58.770
Hello.

32:59.810 --> 33:00.660
Are you

33:00.900 --> 33:01.560
a director?

33:01.610 --> 33:02.070
No.

33:02.750 --> 33:04.010
I'm the screenwriter.

33:04.500 --> 33:05.330
No wonder

33:05.610 --> 33:06.240
I haven’t even gotten close

33:06.240 --> 33:07.750
to you yet,

33:07.750 --> 33:09.660
this strong cultural vibe

33:09.660 --> 33:11.520
is already hitting me in the face.

33:12.550 --> 33:13.150
Thank you.

33:13.530 --> 33:14.730
You live in this room?

33:15.070 --> 33:15.610
Yes.

33:17.330 --> 33:19.060
Could I have your phone number?

33:21.110 --> 33:22.510
I don't have a phone here.

33:22.900 --> 33:23.890
It's fine.

33:24.070 --> 33:25.870
Then I'll leave you to your work.

33:42.380 --> 33:42.940
Sir,

33:43.000 --> 33:45.200
I actually really like literature too.

33:45.900 --> 33:47.160
When you have time,

33:47.660 --> 33:49.220
I'd like to ask for your advice.

33:49.220 --> 33:50.110
Would that be okay?

33:50.110 --> 33:51.270
Sure, no problem.

33:51.720 --> 33:53.020
Sir, I'll be leaving now.

33:53.020 --> 33:53.400
Okay.

33:53.460 --> 33:53.990
Goodbye.

33:54.310 --> 33:54.840
Goodbye.

34:12.250 --> 34:14.550
[At the gate of the textile factory]

34:18.880 --> 34:19.820
[Greeting]

34:20.960 --> 34:21.710
[Greeting]

34:25.090 --> 34:25.570
Ranran,

34:26.460 --> 34:27.190
are you okay?

34:41.860 --> 34:42.790
If you were dead,

34:42.960 --> 34:44.300
could you still make a sound?

34:44.300 --> 34:45.710
I'm sorry, Director.

34:51.219 --> 34:52.219
[Belated Love]

35:04.590 --> 35:07.910
[Belated Love—Xu's Version]

35:08.260 --> 35:13.610
Xu, toughen up!

35:20.610 --> 35:22.050
Speaking...

35:25.820 --> 35:26.370
Sir,

35:27.650 --> 35:28.710
are you home alone?

35:29.480 --> 35:30.610
Have you had dinner?

35:31.260 --> 35:31.880
Not yet.

35:32.190 --> 35:33.230
You work hard on your writing.

35:33.230 --> 35:34.490
You should eat on time.

35:34.710 --> 35:35.570
If you haven't eaten,

35:35.570 --> 35:36.690
let me treat you to dinner.

35:36.690 --> 35:37.150
No need.

35:37.550 --> 35:38.610
I have things to do.

35:38.840 --> 35:39.920
I haven't eaten either.

35:39.920 --> 35:40.590
Let's eat together.

35:40.590 --> 35:42.170
No, there's really no need.

35:42.170 --> 35:42.940
I need to write my script.

35:42.940 --> 35:44.090
A meal won't take

35:44.090 --> 35:44.980
too much time.

35:45.400 --> 35:46.130
Let's eat together.

35:46.130 --> 35:47.610
I just got inspired;

35:47.630 --> 35:49.160
I need to finish it quickly.

35:50.230 --> 35:52.420
Okay, then you keep working
on your writing.

35:52.420 --> 35:54.480
I'll treat you next time you're free.

36:06.820 --> 36:08.350
I'm really not going to eat.

36:09.090 --> 36:10.150
You're not eating?

36:10.860 --> 36:11.300
Eat!

36:11.820 --> 36:12.650
Eat!

36:14.000 --> 36:15.460
I was just reading lines.

36:15.550 --> 36:16.700
Hurry, come in.

36:22.670 --> 36:23.970
This place is not bad.

36:24.730 --> 36:26.130
You keep it pretty clean.

36:26.300 --> 36:27.500
Of course.

36:27.860 --> 36:28.880
I cleaned it up

36:28.880 --> 36:30.140
all by myself.

36:30.550 --> 36:32.110
I'm not a slob.

36:32.670 --> 36:34.440
That mess in Room 108
has nothing to do with me.

36:34.440 --> 36:35.900
Those three made the mess.

36:40.320 --> 36:41.850
You’ll see when you go back.

36:42.000 --> 36:43.300
Room 108 has changed.

36:44.190 --> 36:44.920
Changed how?

36:45.300 --> 36:47.090
Someone who is a neat freak moved in.

36:47.090 --> 36:49.890
The floor is mopped so clean
you can do splits on it.

36:51.070 --> 36:52.000
Isn't that good?

36:53.000 --> 36:54.190
Do you have chopsticks?

36:54.190 --> 36:55.390
Yes, I'll go get them.

37:01.670 --> 37:02.070
Here.

37:07.530 --> 37:09.320
Such a rich meal.

37:09.460 --> 37:10.880
I was cooking for myself.

37:10.940 --> 37:12.170
I accidentally made too much

37:12.170 --> 37:15.300
and couldn't finish it,
so I brought it to share with you.

37:16.420 --> 37:18.340
You accidentally made this much?

37:23.360 --> 37:25.530
Wenzhou food is sweet.

37:25.820 --> 37:27.050
I don't know if you're used to it.

37:27.050 --> 37:28.050
I am.

37:29.570 --> 37:29.980
Try it.

37:31.400 --> 37:32.330
It's delicious!

37:32.690 --> 37:33.860
Is your leg feeling better?

37:33.860 --> 37:34.460
It's fine.

37:35.460 --> 37:37.120
Watch me hop a couple of times.

37:39.130 --> 37:40.150
Don't end up lying on the ground

37:40.150 --> 37:41.280
and unable to get up.

37:43.670 --> 37:44.570
Stop acting.

37:44.820 --> 37:45.530
No, this...

37:49.710 --> 37:51.370
You actually pulled a muscle?

37:51.910 --> 37:52.730
No.

37:52.760 --> 37:53.210
Help me up.

37:53.210 --> 37:55.230
Try walking back and forth.

37:59.420 --> 38:00.400
I'm fine now.

38:04.760 --> 38:05.820
Why are you a screenwriter?

38:05.820 --> 38:07.080
You should be an actor.

38:10.400 --> 38:11.400
This dish is good.

38:11.510 --> 38:12.240
Really good.

38:12.880 --> 38:14.340
Hurry, you should eat too.

38:14.420 --> 38:14.860
Hurry.

38:16.880 --> 38:17.360
Sir,

38:17.460 --> 38:19.590
I got you some food from the cafeteria.

38:20.760 --> 38:22.340
I'm eating.

38:24.340 --> 38:25.670
Oh, you’ve got company?

38:26.590 --> 38:27.940
Then let’s eat together—

38:27.940 --> 38:30.000
I’ll add a couple more dishes for you.

38:37.940 --> 38:40.390
Well, I have class.

38:40.460 --> 38:41.170
You guys eat.

38:41.170 --> 38:42.400
No, no. Zhuang Zhuang.

38:42.400 --> 38:44.460
-I’m going to be late.
-She won't eat?

38:45.500 --> 38:46.400
So many dishes...

38:46.400 --> 38:47.260
Zhuang Zhuang!

38:47.800 --> 38:48.660
Zhuang Zhuang.

38:49.860 --> 38:51.070
You misunderstood.

38:51.860 --> 38:53.060
Misunderstood what?

38:53.130 --> 38:54.940
She and I...

38:57.630 --> 38:58.440
Aren't you helping Mr. He

38:58.440 --> 38:59.280
look after the place?

38:59.280 --> 38:59.880
Go on then.

39:01.190 --> 39:02.520
Don't keep her waiting.

39:13.590 --> 39:14.520
Stop doing that.

39:14.690 --> 39:15.290
You can leave.

39:15.290 --> 39:16.850
Why did your friend leave?

39:16.880 --> 39:17.500
You have so many dishes.

39:17.500 --> 39:18.900
We can't finish them all.

39:19.260 --> 39:20.320
You're not eating?

39:21.050 --> 39:23.310
Why are you asking when you already know?

39:25.360 --> 39:27.160
Then I won't bother you anymore.

39:30.960 --> 39:31.400
Wait.

39:42.860 --> 39:43.340
Take it.

39:43.780 --> 39:45.110
Don't let it go to waste.

39:46.730 --> 39:47.300
Goodbye.

40:01.800 --> 40:02.400
Thank you.

40:07.090 --> 40:07.690
Thank you.

40:15.010 --> 40:15.540
Hey, man,

40:15.820 --> 40:16.710
you can take my seat.

40:16.710 --> 40:17.910
I'm getting off soon.

40:18.940 --> 40:19.600
Have a seat.

40:20.280 --> 40:20.980
Thank you.

40:21.150 --> 40:21.810
No problem.

40:49.800 --> 40:50.300
Sir,

40:51.010 --> 40:52.400
can we switch seats?

40:52.630 --> 40:53.550
Don't you have a seat?

40:53.550 --> 40:54.420
Just sit there.

40:54.710 --> 40:56.000
We know each other.

40:57.170 --> 40:57.710
Do you?

41:02.820 --> 41:03.530
Wait, I mean,

41:03.530 --> 41:04.280
why are you young people

41:04.280 --> 41:05.150
up to no good like this?

41:05.150 --> 41:06.400
No, it's not like that.

41:06.400 --> 41:07.030
Conductor!

41:07.030 --> 41:07.670
No.

41:07.710 --> 41:08.500
Sir.

41:09.380 --> 41:10.440
We know each other.

41:10.820 --> 41:11.500
We do.

41:11.650 --> 41:12.490
You really do?

41:12.550 --> 41:13.420
Yes, we do.

41:15.190 --> 41:16.230
You're a young couple having a spat,

41:16.230 --> 41:17.960
and you're making a fool out of me.

41:17.960 --> 41:18.860
Thanks, sir.

41:25.280 --> 41:26.410
You're so good to me.

41:27.550 --> 41:28.570
Save it.

41:30.690 --> 41:32.570
I really didn't know

41:32.570 --> 41:34.260
that woman yesterday.

41:34.420 --> 41:35.440
She even delivered the food

41:35.440 --> 41:36.500
right to your door.

41:37.570 --> 41:38.670
I guess

41:38.730 --> 41:40.830
she thought I was a teacher,

41:40.960 --> 41:41.630
or a professor.

41:41.630 --> 41:42.760
That's because I stayed in that room.

41:42.760 --> 41:43.470
So she...

41:45.420 --> 41:45.880
Sorry.

41:45.880 --> 41:46.800
It's okay.

41:53.420 --> 41:55.100
You care about me that much?

41:57.670 --> 41:59.470
I just didn't want to waste food.

41:59.800 --> 42:01.300
If you had told me someone
was bringing you food,

42:01.300 --> 42:02.700
I wouldn't have had to...

42:03.820 --> 42:05.980
You went to the market so early

42:06.000 --> 42:06.830
to cook for me?

42:07.130 --> 42:08.530
Don't flatter yourself.

42:12.940 --> 42:13.980
After you left,

42:14.000 --> 42:15.140
I had no appetite.

42:16.170 --> 42:17.670
I put the food

42:18.070 --> 42:19.170
in the fridge.

42:19.840 --> 42:20.880
I couldn't sleep
in the middle of the night,

42:20.880 --> 42:22.210
so I got up and had a bite.

42:22.610 --> 42:24.210
Once I started, I couldn't stop.

42:24.210 --> 42:25.510
I ate until I was stuffed.

42:25.510 --> 42:27.770
There wasn't a single grain of rice left.

42:28.230 --> 42:29.130
Are you a mouse?

42:29.710 --> 42:31.640
You got up in the middle of the night

42:31.760 --> 42:33.570
to eat rice and didn't leave
a single grain?

42:33.570 --> 42:35.320
Well, I had to be full

42:35.380 --> 42:37.440
to figure out how to explain it to you.

42:38.030 --> 42:38.610
It's true.

42:38.610 --> 42:39.380
Even when analyzing a script,

42:39.380 --> 42:41.710
I've never weighed my words so carefully.

42:42.820 --> 42:43.880
You care that much?

42:44.570 --> 42:45.990
Of course I care.

42:46.070 --> 42:48.000
I couldn't let you misunderstand.

42:50.400 --> 42:52.510
Laugh if you want to.

42:52.710 --> 42:53.690
I don't want to.
